<br>
=========================<br>
<br>
I set up a sample here: <!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub6.ezboard.com/bhandofwrath">pub6.ezboard.com/bhandofwrath</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
In this sample the subforums are formated dramatically different from the main forums.  For this to look best I would suggest formating them the same.<br>
<br>
This method requires an additional ez-board for every subforum group. (Avvi already has this set up)<br>
<br>
What you do is in the name of the forum (&quot;General&quot; next to the forum listing, second box from the top. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   not the first box</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->) put something that looks like this:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   '<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub7.ezboard.com/bhandofwrath91496'">pub7.ezboard.com/bhandofwrath91496'</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> class=title&gt;This goes to another boad (sub forums)<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
The bold part is the full address of the ez-board you are using as a sub forum.  It is important to make sure that you use single quotes ( <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   '</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ) and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> double quotes ( <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   &quot;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> ).<br>
<br>
You must leave the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   class=title</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> part in if you want it to be formated like the rest of your forum titles.   Everything after <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   class=title&gt;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> will be the text displayed as the forum listing. <br>
<br>
The only problem I see is I don't know how to link the unread image to the sub-board (once 'mark all as read' has been clicked the forum will always appear 'read'). <br>
<br>
I hope this is helpful. <br>
<br>
More specifically the code you would use as the forum title would be this (or something very close) :<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   <br>
&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href='<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub28.ezboard.com/bavvisioneclassboard'">pub28.ezboard.com/bavvisioneclassboard'</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> class=title&gt;Class Specific Forums<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
